postcontent: Please read the Item Characteristics for important listing details.SpecificationsManufacturer: Smith & WessonModel: 629-1Serial Number: AHS3660 (Early 1980's Production)Frame Size: NCaliber: .44 Remington Magnum / .44 SpecialCapacity: 6 Round CylinderBarrel: 6.5"Front Sight: Red RampedRear Sight: S&W Fully AdjustableFeatures: Target Trigger & HammerGrips: Goncalo Alves Target GripsFinish: Brushed StainlessDescriptionTaken on trade through our retail store, this firearm is in excellent condition overall. It does show light signs of being carried and used here and there but here is no major marks to speak of. The action of this Smith is amazing, smooth as glass cylinder and perfect trigger lock-up. Pictures best describe this firearm for exactly what it is and what you will receive! Smith & Wesson's production of a large N-frame revolver chambered for the .44 Remington Magnum cartridge began in 1955. It was not until 1957 that this revolver received the name "Model 29". First offered in 1978, the Smith & Wesson Model 629 was essentially the stainless steel version of the Model 29. The 629 model designation derives from Smith & Wesson's practice of denoting a stainless steel version of one of their already existing designs by placing a 6 in front of the model number of the original weapon. Elmer Keith's achievements in maximizing the power and performance of the .44 Special was the inspiration and driving force behind the introduction of the .44 Magnum by Smith & Wesson. His intention for the new round was for it to be used in sidearms for hunters of large, dangerous game, rather than for self-defense, though with today's specialty cartridges, it can be a good defensive round. It remained primarily the province of handgun enthusiasts, some law enforcement personnel and hunters until 1971, when Clint Eastwood made it famous as "the most powerful handgun in the world" in the movie Dirty Harry. After the movie's release, retailers had trouble keeping the Model 29 in stock.

title: For Sale:  Clean KSG with Extras
postcontent: For sale I have a Kel-Tec KSG (Gen 1).  It has been cleaned after every use and is a lot of fun to shoot.  My wife and I just had our first kid so I'm selling a few toys that just don't serve as much of a purpose as others do.  As you will see in the extras I have installed a choke adapter on this gun.  As it happens this gun is amazing with clay pigeon shooting.  I ran a vortex optic on it and it was TOO EASY.  Also, if you like attention, people will want to see the gun at the clay range as it looks nothing like anything else.  You will also see I've bought and installed an extended top rail.  It may not seem like a big difference to you but this allows you to have a good long sight radius with BUIS and an optic.  The added benefit is if you have a folding rear BUIS it won't hang off the back of the rail and be in danger of getting broken off.  In all, this gun is super fun to shoot and I hate to see it go but family comes first.  As for the extras, they are listed below at their MSRP not including any shipping costs or tax I paid: Rear QD Sling Mount- $29.99 Front QD Sling Mount Rail Mount- $18.95 Extended Top Rail- $99.95 Barrel Nut Removal Tool (To replace the barrel nut with the choke adapter)- $29.95 Choke Adapter- $56.00 KSG Handstop- $10.00  Total of $244.84 in extras!  These guns themselves are running around $650 new and I understand you may not want all of these extras so I'm pricing my gun quite competitively.  Please let me know what questions you have!  This weapon does come with the original Manual.NO TRADES

title: For Sale:  Potential CZ P10c owners beware..!
postcontent: The handgun is absolutely awesome but being that it is so new there is bound to be some teething pain.Anyone looking to purchase one needs to check the firing pin when the gun is locked open and ensure you cannot push it to the right because this is what's causing the gun to keep from going back into battery on one out of every three currently out.It essentially makes the gun a paper weight until you're able to rack it enough times to correct the pin.. it is a design flaw that they are aware.. it using a piece of plastic to offset the pin so you will be able to rotate it to the right and there is quite a bit of wiggle..please check YouTube for the actual description and what it looks like!There are two or three other issues to do with the rear slide plate and the area around the roll pin..near the takedown..I love all MY CZ..and the GEN 2 P07 is absolute rock-solid and proven!..but they have some issues to work out with this one..
